               <head>Pentateuch</head>
                    
               
               
               
               <msContents class="lccn.loc.gov/n79066420 ark:/81055/vdc_100022569904.0x000003" rend="visible">
                        
                  
                  
                  
                  <summary>Pentateuch with Targum Onḳelos in the margin, the Hafṭarot with
                            the Five Scrolls in the margin, with punctuation and accents.</summary>
                        
                  
                  
                  
                  <textLang mainLang="he" otherLangs="tmr-Hebr">Hebrew, Aramaic</textLang>
                        
                  
                  
                  
                  <msItem n="0" rend="visible" class="lccn.loc.gov/n79066420">
                            
                     
                     
                     
                     <locus from="1r" to="301v"/>
                            
                     
                     
                     
                     <title xml:lang="he-Latn-x-lc">Torah, hafṭarot ṿe-megilot </title>
                            
                     
                     
                     
                     <title xml:lang="he">תורה, הפטרות ומגילות </title>
                            
                     
                     
                     
                     <textLang mainLang="he" otherLangs="tmr-Hebr">Hebrew, Aramaic</textLang>
                            
                     
                     
                     
                     <note>
                        
                        
                        
                        <p>The Pentateuch and the Hafṭarot have Targum in the margins.
                                    </p>
                        
                        
                        
                        <p>The manuscript is imperfect at the beginning and at the
                                    end, with many leaves missing after folios 8, 56 and 59.
                                    </p>
                        
                        
                        
                        <p>Outer half of folio 218 is from another Ashkenazi
                                    manuscript (?), containing the last end of Numers (from the
                                    middle of Num. 36:9 until the end of the book), and a scribal
                                    formula: <quote xml:lang="he">חזק ונתחזק הסופר לא יזק לא היום לא
                                        לעול' עד שיעלה חמור בסולם. נשלם ספר במדבר הבורא יאמר לכל
                                        צרותינו עבר א'ב'כ'י'ר</quote>. Folio 87 is also an addition
                                    probably from the same Ashkenazi manuscript. </p>
                        
                        
                        
                        <p>There is a
                                    similarity in punctuation and accents to MS Harley 5683 (George Margoliouth, Catalogue of the Hebrew and Samaritan Manuscripts in the British Museum, 4 vols (London: British Museum, 1899-1935; vols I-III repr. 1965); IV, Introduction, Indexes, ed. by Jacob Leveen (London: British Museum, 1977), no. 69.), cf. <ref target="Ginsburg_1880" type="number">7</ref>. </p>
                     
                     
                     
                     </note>
                            
                     
                     
                     
                     <colophon xml:lang="he">מניין פסוקי מאלה שמות אלף ומאה וחמשים זה סימן י'
                                צ' ח' ק' בן שמחה ביום תתקעו מפרט.<locus n="114r-v"/>
                     
                     
                     
                     </colophon>
                            
                     
                     
                     
                     <colophon xml:lang="he">חזק ונתחזק שמחה ב"ר יוסף<locus n="271v"/>
                     
                     
                     
                     </colophon>
                        
                  
                  
                  
